down at a piece of parchment in her palm. &quot;Yes, I think this is it.&quot;<br>
Taking in a deep breath, the older woman tucked a few strands of thick curly hair behind one ear and made her way into the tavern.  Finding it empty, a brow rose, &quot;my my, this will be interesting.&quot;<br>
Moving along the bar, she ran her fingertip along it's worn surface, absently she rubbed her finger and thumb together as pale eyes took in the expanse of the common room itself. With a satisfied nod, Cyrene went behind the bar to check the stock of supplies and a thin smirk appeared as both brows rose in surprise.<br>
&quot;Well, this will never do,&quot; without so much as to find out where she would be staying, or even meeting the Queens, she rolled up her sleeves, grabbed a bucket and water, parchment and quill to set off to work.<br>
