<br>
Ara walked over to the bar and smiled to the woman, &quot;Hello, I am Arahuta&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(8/22/02 9:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Labrys Amazon Tavern</span><hr size=1> &quot;Oh...by the gods...&quot; Cyrene wiped her brow and glanced out the window, by the looks of the light she'd been working for a few candlemarks without realizing the passing of time.<br>
The older woman glanced up from behind the bar, the sleeves of her dark blue tunic rolled up past the elbow.  Beads of sweat dripped from the mass of curls over her brow.  A hand reached back to push the hair off her face, tucking the thick ebon behind her ears.  Pale, depthless azure eyes searched the room as she heard the old hinges protest against the movment of the door.  A bright smile appeared across her features at spotting the dark skinned woman. She wiped a bar towel between her palms.<br>
&quot;Welcome,&quot; her voice held a warm timber, rich and deep for one of her size, just over 5 feet when she was in boots.<br>
Dressed in a tunic and long leather skirt, the tendress seemed to exude warmth and welcome, her eyes showing every bit the deep fires of a hearth, yet betraying nothing.<br>
&quot;By the gods...I'm late aren't I?&quot; she asked the stranger as if the dark amazon would know the answer, or even have a clue as to what she ment.<br>
&quot;The festival, it's tonight...are you going?&quot; Quickly rolling down her sleeves she moved out from behind the bar, brows knit in worry. &quot;I don't even know the way.&quot; Smoothing a few none existant wrinkles in her tunic she walked up to the Amazon.<br>
&quot;I'm sorry, ignore what I just said.  I'm Cyrene, and I'm being rude.&quot; Glancing up at the Amazon she offered a full smile and extended her arm in greeting. &quot;It's nice to meet you Arahuta.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/handsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#993300>(8/22/02 10:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The visitor</span><hr size=1> Arahuta took the woman's arm and shook it slightly.  &quot;It is very nice to meet you Cyrene.  I am afraid I had not heard about the festival.  I was just on my way back to Themiscrya from a journey.&quot;  <br>
<br>
She stepped back and smiled softly.  Her voice and accent was unlike anything Cyrene had heard before.  &quot;But, if you like.  I can take you to the city.&quot;  <br>
