&quot;I have a horse, she's not the fastest.  I hope that won't slow you down too much.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/handsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#993300>(8/23/02 10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/arahuta.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The visitor</span><hr size=1> &quot;It is no problem,&quot; Ara smiled as she began to lead Cyrene out of the Labrys.  &quot;The village is not that far from here.  And I am actually on foot.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Motioning for Cyrene to get on her horse, Arahuta lead then lead them away from the Tavern and into the woods.  The way to Themiscrya was covered.  And only the amazons could read the paths.  There was no direct way into Themiscrya.  Themiscryans had long learned to not walk in each other's footsteps and take different ways thru the forest to the city.    Ara lead the way with Cyrene on horseback behind her, pushing back the vines and walking around sharp bushes.  Until the found themselves, suddenly hitting a clearing.  Before them was the active city of Themiscrya.  Ara smiled seeing her adopted home.  &quot;Welcome to the City of Amazons.&quot;  She said to Cyrene.  &quot;Looks like the festival has begun.&quot;  Ara could see amazons moving towards the great pavilion.  &quot;We better hurry.&quot;  <br>
<br>
