<br>
Cyrene hardly noticed where she was going in the dark she allowed her gentle mare to find their way back to the tavern.  Finding the common room empty, she wasn't surprised.  The festival was still going, and she couldn't find the energy to stay for a moment longer.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're bones are getting old,&quot; she laughed to herself as she took care of the mare for the night, sending her into the small enclosed area and spending over a candlemark giving the mare a well deserved brush-down.<br>
<br>
Dusting off her hands, the older woman made her way back to the tavern, opening the side door that lead to the kitchen, she hummed a joyful tune under her breath. She allowed herself to finish organizing a few things in the back room before moving out to find the room she'd be staying in while with her new sisters.<br>
<br>
Finding the room wasn't as hard as she thought.  It was simply furnished, which she enjoyed, with a hearth off to the east wall for when it grew cold.  Pleased to find her one trunk of personal items was already in the room, she moved over to it and crouched down to open the chest. &quot;Thank you,&quot; she whispered a thanks to the air, for she had no idea which Amazon to thank for hauling up the heavy chest from the shores of the Black Sea.<br>
<br>
Even though she was tired, she spend some time putting her things away, getting to know the place she would be spending a lot of time.<br>
<br>
Sometime passed and she placed her palms on her hips, a wide grin on her lips as she glanced around the room.  Turning to the window, her smile faded to a grin of hidden sadness. &quot;Well my children, I think you'd be proud of your old Mother..where ever you are.&quot;<br>
<br>
Brows furrowed as she pushed those thoughts from her mind and moved off to get ready for bed, a haunting melody tickling the back of her throat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 652<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 5:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Next morning</span><hr size=1> Varia hadn't been to the labrys in what seemed like forever. It was the place she'd first hung around when joining the Sisters of Themiscrya... and truth be told, she missed those days. Pushing open the door carefully she stepped inside, letting it creak closed behind her and swing a few times before settling. Brushing her hands on her leather pants she looked around, taking a deep breath, inhaling the scent of the first place since her mother had died that felt like home. <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 5:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipoli