<br>
Moving to the bar she reached for a rag and wiped her palms. &quot;I hope you enjoyed the festival last night.  Hmm..if you enjoyed it a bit too much I have something to help.&quot; Motions over to a steaming pot to her right. &quot;Or perhaps I could interest you in a morning meal?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 6:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Curiosity got the best of the Queen of the Gods, that day.  Watching her white peacock in the gardens, something called her to the reflecting pool.  Without sound, she moved towards the pool.   The long shimmery dress barely gave any hint that the Goddess was even walking.  Cold frigid blue eyes set upon the pool, not leaving it's surface as she slowely neared it.  And then she stopped.  Looking down into the reflection, the Queen's right brow slowely crooked upward in a sharp slant.  A long arm and slender dark sleeved arm reached out to dance pale digits across the refection causing a small ripple.  <br>
<br>
The front door and windows of the Labrys suddenly burst open with a chilled breeze behind them that moved about the room touching the occupants.  As quickly as it moved in, the windows and door closed to silence. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 7:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> The sudden outburst caused Cyrene's knuckles to turn white as she gripped the counter to keep from jumping.  Gasping for air as the chill touched her skin, she trembled and held on.<br>
Then it was gone.<br>
Pale eyes narrowed as she glared at the doors and windows, confused she grasped her upper arms in an attempt to warm them.<br>
&quot;I'm new here, does that happen often?&quot; There was a familiar sent carried with the wind, something she could just about put her finger on before it skittered away into her consciousness.<br>
&quot;Something to do with the sea air hitting the mountain air?&quot; Cyrene cast a questioning look at Varia. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 658<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 4:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Varia did jump at that breeze, and she squeaked too. Then shaking her head to Cyrene's questions she eyed the windows warily. "Bet it was one of the gods... they like to sneak around like that." She eyed once more and then double checked the locks, finding them secure. "Yep, it was one of the gods." <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 9:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Cyrene didn't know whether she could be confused, hurt, or angry, so she was all three at once.  She'd watched Varia move around the room, and even before she spoke those words, she had a suspicion.  Though she had no idea which god would...eh.<br>
<br>
Pushing the thoughts from her mind she shrugged and laughed.  &quot;Well, next time they'll have to leave their name.  I'll leave an offering for them in thanks for helping me dust the tavern.&quot; Offering a salute to the air, the older woman smiled at Varia and moved over to the pot of stew to give it a stir.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, where were we? Yes, you wanting some breakfast?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 10:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> "Your welcome," came a voice from near the unused hearth.  The fact was that the immortal hadn't left the tavern.  She had watched for a bit until she decided to materialize.  There was a cry of a peafowl in the distance. Shimmering in the tavern, the Queen of the Gods appeared wearing her sparkling black dress.  The collar of small peacock feathers danced around her pale white neck.  Her eyes danced from Varia and then to Cyrene.  Their blue colour so cold that they were almost white.  "Tho dusting isn't one of my secret passions." <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 666<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 10:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Varia nodded to Cyrene. "Hungry as Hades," she said. "Though I doubt it was he who graced us with his presence," she chuckled. Then hearing Hera's voice she looked over and gave a smile, wave, and a little bow. "Greetings, Queen Hera," she said, as she sidled on over to a table to have a seat, getting out some dinars to pay for breakfast. <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 11:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The sound of silence.</span><hr size=1> Cyrene dropped the bowl she'd just picked up.  Grasping the necklace around her throat, the older woman turned slightly grey, then lost most of the color all together.  With a blink, she stepped back, and closed her gaping mouth.<br>
<br>
Shifting a quick glance to Varia, she gathered two bowls and filled them with the famous brew.  Rabbit stew spiced with onions and curry, thick root vegetables and small bits of hard dried bread. A favorite dish people were known to make a day's detour from their travels to stop at her tavern.<br>
<br>
Without thought she placed the dish in front of Varia, and the empty space beside her near the Queen of the Gods.  Turning back 'round she poured tankards of water, those as well were placed next to the bowls.  A plate of bread and sweet hard cheese between the two bowls.<br>
<br>
Turning her attention once more to the Queen of the gods, pale azure defensive, apprehensive, yet showing no disrespect.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you,&quot; the older woman spoke softly as she accepted the dinars from Varia never allowing her eyes to leave the Olympian's.  After a moment, she found her heart catch in her throat on it's way up to escape the confines of her chest.  She had to break contact from the unearthly gaze and found solace in wiping a quite clean spot on the counter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 11:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/lilhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sound of silence.</span><hr size=1> Slowely she turned her eyes to Varia and gave her a greeting, "Hello, Varia."  Then her head tilted towards the tavern keeper who seemed determined to finish her tasks despite the Goddesses appearance.  Hera could sense and see Cyrene's nervousness.  A hard to come by smile attempted to rise her lips, but they moved only ever slightly.<br>
<br>
"I was told that you needed to speak to me," Her voice was cold, despite the genuine attempt at being nice.  Hera's eyes not leaving Cyrene.<br>
<br>
